genresAdvancedInfo.name: botswana hip hop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Botswana hip hop is a relatively new genre that emerged in the late 1990s and early 2000s in Botswana, Africa. Influenced by American hip hop, Botswana hip hop artists like Vee Mampeezy and Zeus have developed their own unique sound that incorporates traditional African rhythms and languages.
